---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Backup & PITR" 
  description="Interactive visualization of Backup & PITR"
  breadcrumbs={[{label:"Home",href:"/"},{label:"TiDB",href:"/tidb/"},{label:"Backup & PITR",href:"/tidb/backup-pitr/"}]}
>
  <div class="viz-container">
    <header class="viz-header">
      <h1>💾 Backup & PITR</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Full Backups, Incremental Backups, and Point-in-Time Recovery</p>
    </header>

    <section class="overview-section">
      <div class="overview-card">
        <p>TiDB supports <strong>full backups</strong> (snapshot of all data), <strong>incremental backups</strong> (changes since last backup), and <strong>PITR</strong> (Point-in-Time Recovery) using change logs. BR (Backup & Restore) tool takes distributed snapshots across all TiKV nodes in parallel. PITR uses <em>log backup</em> — continuously streaming change logs to storage. Recover to any second within the log window.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    
    <section class="items-section">
      <h2>💾 Backup Types</h2>
      <div class="items-grid">
        <div class="item-card" style="grid-column: span 3"><ul class="item-list"><li>Full: complete snapshot, ~minutes for TB</li><li>Incremental: only changed SST files</li><li>Log backup: continuous CDC-like stream</li><li>All stored on S3/GCS/local FS</li><li>BR tool for backup/restore</li></ul></div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="items-section">
      <h2>⏰ PITR Flow</h2>
      <div class="items-grid">
        <div class="item-card" style="grid-column: span 3"><ul class="item-list"><li>Full backup at T0</li><li>Log backup streams T0 → T_now continuously</li><li>Disaster at T_crash</li><li>Restore full backup T0</li><li>Replay logs T0 → T_target (before crash)</li><li>Cluster restored to exact second</li></ul></div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="items-section">
      <h2>✅ Best Practices</h2>
      <div class="items-grid">
        <div class="item-card" style="grid-column: span 3"><ul class="item-list"><li>Full backup: weekly or daily</li><li>Log backup: always running</li><li>Test restores regularly!</li><li>Store backups in different region</li><li>Monitor backup lag (should be <5min)</li></ul></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="explain-section">
      <div class="explain-grid">
        <div class="explain-card highlight-card"><h3>💡 Distributed Snapshot</h3><p>BR doesn't lock the database. It takes a consistent snapshot using TiDB's MVCC — read at a specific timestamp while writes continue. Each TiKV node backs up its own Regions in parallel. TB-scale backups complete in minutes.</p></div>
<div class="explain-card"><h3>⚡ Log Backup</h3><p>Each TiKV node streams its Raft log changes to external storage. This is the PITR foundation — it captures every write. Overhead is minimal (~5% throughput impact). Without log backup, you can only restore to full/incremental backup points.</p></div>
<div class="explain-card"><h3>📊 Recovery Time</h3><p>Full restore: proportional to data size (~10 min for 1TB on fast storage). Log replay: proportional to log volume. If you did a full backup 6 hours ago and have 100GB of logs, expect ~15-20 min total recovery time.</p></div>
<div class="explain-card"><h3>⚠️ GC & Backups</h3><p>Backups need to read at a specific timestamp. If GC cleans up versions before the backup reads them → backup fails. BR automatically adjusts GC safe point during backup. Don't set tikv_gc_life_time too low if you run large backups.</p></div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="viz-footer">
      <p>Based on <a href="https://docs.pingcap.com/tidb/stable/backup-and-restore-overview" target="_blank">official documentation</a></p>
    </footer>

    <div class="share-buttons">
      <span>Share:</span>
      <a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Backup%20%26%20PITR&url=https://systeminternals.dev/tidb/backup-pitr/" target="_blank" class="share-btn">𝕏 Twitter</a>
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url=https://systeminternals.dev/tidb/backup-pitr/" target="_blank" class="share-btn">in LinkedIn</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.viz-container{max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto}.viz-header{text-align:center;margin-bottom:40px}.viz-header h1{font-size:2.5rem;margin-bottom:10px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,#a78bfa, #818cf8);-webkit-background-clip:text;-webkit-text-fill-color:transparent;background-clip:text}.subtitle{color:#888;font-size:1.1rem}h2{font-size:1.5rem;color:#fff;margin-bottom:12px}.section-desc{color:#888;margin-bottom:24px}
.overview-section{margin-bottom:50px}.overview-card{background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(167,139,250,0.1),rgba(167,139,250,0.03));border:1px solid rgba(167,139,250,0.3);border-radius:16px;padding:24px 28px;font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.8;color:#ccc}.overview-card strong{color:#fff}.overview-card em{color:#a78bfa;font-style:normal;font-weight:500}.overview-card code{background:rgba(0,0,0,0.3);padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.9rem;color:#a78bfa}
.flow-section{margin-bottom:50px}.flow-steps{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0}.flow-step{display:flex;gap:14px;padding:12px 16px;border-left:3px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1)}.flow-step:nth-child(1){border-left-color:#a78bfa}.fs-icon{font-size:1.1rem}.fs-text{font-size:0.9rem;color:#ccc}
.items-section{margin-bottom:50px}.items-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:16px}.item-card{background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);border-radius:14px;padding:20px}.item-card h3{font-size:1rem;color:#fff;margin-bottom:10px}.item-list{list-style:none;padding:0}.item-list li{font-size:0.8rem;color:#aaa;padding:4px 0;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.04)}.item-list li:last-child{border-bottom:none}
.explain-section{margin-bottom:50px}.explain-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:20px}.explain-card{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.03);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);border-radius:14px;padding:24px}.explain-card h3{font-size:1rem;color:#fff;margin-bottom:10px}.explain-card p{color:#aaa;line-height:1.6;font-size:0.9rem}.explain-card strong{color:#a78bfa}.explain-card code{background:rgba(0,0,0,0.3);padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.85rem;color:#a78bfa}.highlight-card{background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(167,139,250,0.08),rgba(167,139,250,0.04));border-color:rgba(167,139,250,0.3)}
.viz-footer{text-align:center;color:#666;font-size:0.9rem;padding:20px 0;border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);margin-bottom:30px}.viz-footer a{color:#a78bfa}.share-buttons{display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;gap:16px}.share-buttons span{color:#666}.share-btn{padding:10px 20px;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.1);border-radius:8px;color:#fff;font-size:0.9rem;transition:background 0.2s}.share-btn:hover{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.2)}
@media(max-width:768px){.viz-header h1{font-size:1.8rem}.items-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}.explain-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
</style>
